public class OperatorsExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // arithmetic operators
        int num1 = 10;
        int num2 = 5;

        System.out.println("Addition: " + (num1 + num2));
        System.out.println("Subtraction: " + (num1 - num2));
        System.out.println("Multiplication: " + (num1 * num2));
        System.out.println("Division: " + (num1 / num2));
        System.out.println("Modulus: " + (num1 % num2));

        // relational operators
        int num3 = 6;
        int num4 = 6;

        System.out.println("Equality: " + (num3 == num4));
        System.out.println("Inequality: " + (num3 != num4));
        System.out.println("Greater than: " + (num3 > num4));
        System.out.println("Less than: " + (num3 < num4));
        System.out.println("Greater than or equal to: " + (num3 >= num4));
        System.out.println("Less than or equal to: " + (num3 <= num4));

        // logical operators
        boolean isTrue = true;
        boolean isFalse = false;

        System.out.println("Logical AND: " + (isTrue && isFalse));
        System.out.println("Logical OR: " + (isTrue || isFalse));
        System.out.println("Logical NOT: " + (!isFalse));

        // bitwise operators
        int num5 = 10;
        int num6 = 6;

        System.out.println("Bitwise AND: " + (num5 & num6));
        System.out.println("Bitwise OR: " + (num5 | num6));
        System.out.println("Bitwise XOR: " + (num5 ^ num6));
        System.out.println("Bitwise NOT: " + (~num5));
        System.out.println("Left shift: " + (num5 << 1));
        System.out.println("Right shift: " + (num5 >> 1));
        System.out.println("Unsigned right shift: " + (num5 >>> 1));
    }
}
```

This program demonstrates the use of arithmetic, relational, logical, and bitwise operators. It outputs the results of these operations to the console. The output of this program would be:

