public class StringOperationsExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // initializing two strings
        String str1 = "Hello";
        String str2 = "World";

        // concatenating two strings
        String str3 = str1 + " " + str2;
        System.out.println("Concatenated string: " + str3);

        // getting the length of a string
        int strLength = str3.length();
        System.out.println("String length: " + strLength);

        // converting a string to uppercase and lowercase
        String str4 = "java programming";
        String str5 = str4.toUpperCase();
        String str6 = str4.toLowerCase();
        System.out.println("Original string: " + str4);
        System.out.println("Uppercase string: " + str5);
        System.out.println("Lowercase string: " + str6);

        // substring operation
        String str7 = "apple";
        String str8 = str7.substring(1, 4);
        System.out.println("Original string: " + str7);
        System.out.println("Substring from index 1 to 4: " + str8);

        // checking if a string contains a certain substring
        String str9 = "The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog";
        boolean containsFox = str9.contains("fox");
        boolean containsCat = str9.contains("cat");
        System.out.println("Original string: " + str9);
        System.out.println("Contains 'fox'?: " + containsFox);
        System.out.println("Contains 'cat'?: " + containsCat);
    }
}
```

This program demonstrates various string operations in Java, including concatenation, length, conversion to uppercase and lowercase, substring, and substring search. It outputs the results of these operations to the console. The output of this program would be:

```
